==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tiffany
<hw>Tif"fa*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tiffenay</ets>; cf. OF. <ets>tiffe</ets> ornament,
<ets>tiffer</ets> to adjust, adorn. See <er>Tiff</er> to dress.]</ety>
<def>A species of gause, or very silk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The smoke of sulphur . . . is commonly used by women to whiten
<qex>tiffanies</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiffany</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tiffany
<hw>Tif"fa*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[After <person>Louis
Comfort <etsep>Tiffany</etsep></person>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>made of
stained glass by, or in the style of objects made by, <person>Louis C.
<etsep>Tiffany</etsep></person>; <as>as, a <ex>Tiffany</ex>
lamp</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made by or purchased from the
<corpn><etsep>Tiffany</etsep> corporation</corpn> (with headquarters in
New York City); <as>as, <ex>Tiffany</ex> jewelry</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiffin</ent>⟦br⟧
